The '''Botanical Museum''' in [[Copenhagen]] originated as a part of the [[Copenhagen Botanical Garden]], which was established in 1600. It was later separated as an independent institutiuon. Since 2004, the Botanical Museum forms part of the [[Natural History Museum of Denmark]] under the [[University of Copenhagen]]. It does not have exhibitions open to the public.
The collections contain many [[type specimen]]s and vast collections from around the world.
