'''Escola da Ponte''' (English: '''School of the Bridge''') is an [[open plan school]]<ref>[https://www.oecd.org/portugal/41533062.pdf Open Plan Schools in Portugal: Failure or Innovation?, by Miguel Martinho and José Freire da Silva, PEB Exchange 2008/12, OECD 2008]</ref> in an [[elementary school]], located in [[São Tomé de Negrelos]], [[Portugal]], which was started by [[José Francisco Pacheco]] in 1976 and follows the principles of [[democratic education]]. The school is organized and totally run by students, mainly governed by a weekly [[deliberative assembly]]<ref>[https://soundout.org/escola-da-ponte/ Escola da Ponte,  Adam Fletcher, May 12, 2015]</ref> with them and the [[professors]] and the [[parents]]. Students also there are not divided in [[Class (education)|classes]] but in dynamic groups, and they choose what to study having as the main criteria, what they want to learn.<ref>[https://openideo.com/challenge/youth-employment/inspiration/a-new-education-is-possible- A new education is possible, Written by Maria Occarina Macedo, May 30, 2012]</ref>

It has embodied [[Meaningful Student Involvement]] in classrooms successfully.<ref>[https://soundout.org/escola-da-ponte/ Escola da Ponte,  Adam Fletcher, May 12, 2015]</ref>

