[[File:Gordon Research Conference on Nucleic Acids, New Hampton 1964 Wellcome L0042631.jpg|right|thumb|Gordon Research Conference, 1964]]
'''Gordon Research Conferences''' are a group of prestigious international [[scientific conference]]s organized by a [[non-profit organization]] of the same name. The conference topics cover frontier research in the [[biology|biological]], [[chemistry|chemical]], and [[physics|physical]] sciences, and their related technologies. The conferences have been held since 1931, and have expanded to almost 200 conferences per year. Conference locations are chosen partly for their scenic and often isolated nature, to encourage an informal community atmosphere. Contributions are "off-record" to encourage free discussion, often of unpublished research. Conferences were extended to cover [[science education]] in 1991.<ref>{{cite journal|title = First Gordon Research Conference on Science Education|journal = [[J. Chem. Educ.]]|year = 1991|volume = 68|issue = 11|page = 901|doi = 10.1021/ed068p901|bibcode = 1991JChEd..68..901. }}</ref> The conference topics are regularly publicised in the journal ''[[Science (journal)|Science]]'': 2017<ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 355|pages = 848&ndash;870|year = 2017|doi = 10.1126/science.355.6327.848}}</ref>, 2015,<ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 347|pages = 888&ndash;912|year = 2015|doi = 10.1126/science.347.6224.888}}</ref> 2010,<ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 327|pages = 708&ndash;734|year = 2010|doi = 10.1126/science.327.5966.708|bibcode = 2010Sci...327..708.|issue=5966}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 329|pages = 1362&ndash;1372|year = 2010|doi = 10.1126/science.329.5997.1362|bibcode = 2010Sci...329.1362.|issue=5997}}</ref> 2009,<ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 323|pages = 1084&ndash;1109|year = 2009|doi = 10.1126/science.323.5917.1084|issue=5917}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 325|pages = 1276&ndash;1288|year = 2009|doi = 10.1126/science.325_1276|issue = 5945}}</ref> 2008,<ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 319|pages = 637&ndash;661|year = 2008|doi = 10.1126/science.319.5863.637|issue=5863}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 319|page = 1310|year = 2008|doi = 10.1126/science.319.5868.1310|issue=5868}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 321|pages = 1366&ndash;1373|year = 2008|doi = 10.1126/science.321.5894.1366|issue=5894}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 322|page = 974|year = 2008|doi = 10.1126/science.322.5903.974|issue=5903}}</ref> 2007,<ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 315|pages = 671&ndash;693|year = 2007|doi = 10.1126/science.315.5812.671|issue=5812}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 317|pages = 1407&ndash;1415|year = 2007|doi = 10.1126/science.317.5843.1407|issue=5843}}</ref> and 2006.<ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 311|pages = 676&ndash;699|year = 2006|doi = 10.1126/science.311.5761.676|issue=5761}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 314|pages = 314&ndash;322|year = 2006|doi = 10.1126/science.314.5797.314|issue=5797}}</ref> <ref>{{cite journal|title = Gordon Research Conferences|journal = Science|volume = 314|pages = 1315&ndash;1316|year = 2006|doi = 10.1126/science.314.5803.1315|issue=5803}}</ref>
==History==
The forerunner of the Gordon Conferences was the summer sessions held at the chemistry department of [[Johns Hopkins University]] in the late 1920s. By 1931 this had evolved into a graduate seminar that was also attended by external participants. The Gordon Research Conferences were initiated by Prof. [[Neil Gordon]] while at the Johns Hopkins University.<ref name="jhist">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1021/ed075p1373 | title = Journal History: Guiding the Journal of Chemical Education | journal = [[Journal of Chemical Education]] | volume = 75 | pages = 1373–1380 | year = 1998| bibcode = 1998JChEd..75.1373. }}</ref>
